data.title: Preity Zinta and husband Gene Goodenough meet Dalai Lama in Dharamshala: ‘So grateful…’
data.meta_description: Preity Zinta and her husband Gene Goodenough recently met Dalai Lama in Dharamshala and shared pictures of the same on Instagram. The actress wrote in the caption, ‘Ending IPL in Dharamshala was not what I hoped for but meeting his Holiness The Dalai Lama in Dharamshala was everything I hoped for. So grateful we got to spend some time with him as he shared pearls of wisdom & laughter with us.’ In the pictures, we can see Preity and Gene having conversations and sharing some laughs with the religious leader. The couple was in Dharamshala for Preity’s IPL team Punjab Kings’ match against Rajasthan Royals which they lost resulting in their exit from the tournament. For more news and updates, stay tuned to ETimes.
